{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c7cd366d-0504-4d91-86ea-427c06e3c9c8","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nMTP options go after `--` because on .NET 8 `dotnet test` still uses the VSTest orchestration layer; the `--` forwards arguments to the MTP test host. You'll also need the corresponding NuGet packages in your test project (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3c557322-c8e3-4faf-9625-dcc2cd86f705","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (actually stays the same when using `dotnet test`, but if using the native executable it's `--treenode-filter`)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you configure it differently\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nNow I need to clarify the distinction between running through `dotnet test` versus the native executable, since the option syntax differs. With .NET 8, you'd typically still use `dotnet test` as your entry point, though the underlying runner has changed.\n\nFor .NET 8 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I can pass the new options after `--` when using `dotnet test`, or run the test host directly. The command would pass the tree node filter, reporting, coverage collection, and the new dump options through that separator. But I should double-check whether `--filter` still works with the MSTest runner in this context. Continuing with the blame options and then constructing the full command with all the MTP equivalents. I need to verify the exact tree node filter syntax since it uses a path-like structure with trait filtering, and I want to make sure I'm getting the Category filter right for the Integration tests.","outputTokens":1314,"requestId":"0434:1CDF9E:1E85202:22571C6:69E81A4D"},"id":"435b4fd6-f5ec-4c5c-802d-94b06064b4ec","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:29.532Z","parentId":"33e69db0-584b-4885-9ba8-67f67ed02307"}
